children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Feb. 5, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/210"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–210","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/31"},"text":"90 Stat. 31","children":[],"tail":", § 704(a) (4th–last sentences); added "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Jan. 14, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/468/s301/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–468, § 301(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2549"},"text":"96 Stat. 2549","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsections (a) and (f), the text of 45:854(a) (2d sentence cl. (3)(A)) is omitted as executed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(1), before clause (A), the text of 45:854(a) (1st sentence) is omitted as surplus because of section 24902(a) of the revised title. In clause (B)(i), the words “if the National Railroad Passenger Corporation receives notification on or before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-06-01"},"text":"June 1, 1983","children":[],"tail":", from . . . that such State has approved” and “and if such Corporation determines that such plan is feasible” are omitted as executed. The words “rehabilitation and other . . . (including upgrading track and the signal system, ensuring safety at public and private highway and pedestrian crossings by improving signals or eliminating such crossings, and the improvement of operational portions of stations related to intercity rail passenger service)” are omitted as surplus. In clause (C), before subclause (i), the words “with respect to the main line of the Northeast Corridor” are omitted as surplus. In subclauses (i), (ii), (iv)–(viii), (xv), and (xvii), the word “Washington” is omitted as surplus. In subclause (xx), the words “at locations” are omitted as surplus."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(2)(C), the words “passenger radio mobile telephone service on high-speed rail passenger transportation” are substituted for “high-speed rail passenger rail telephone service” for consistency in this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(2)(D), the word “rail” is added for consistency in the revised title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “After the conveyance of rail properties, pursuant to section 303(b) of the Regional Rail Reorganization Act of 1973 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s743/b"},"text":"45 U.S.C. 743(b)","children":[],"tail":") and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s851/b"},"text":"section 851(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted as executed. The words “remain available to” and “the purpose of performing” are omitted as surplus."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “that portion of . . . issued by the National Railroad Passenger Corporation and” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e)(1), the words “to be appropriated”, “undertaken or viewed as”, “entitled”, and “prepared for the United States Department of Transportation, Federal Railroad Administration, Northeast Corridor Improvement Project, in cooperation with the Federal Railroad Administration and the National Railroad Passenger Corporation (Amtrak), by Deleuw, Cather/Parsons, NECIP architect/engineer” are omitted as surplus. The words “for which amounts are authorized under” are substituted for “described in” for clarity. The words “for expenditure” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (g), the text of 45:854(a) (3d, 5th, and last sentences) is omitted as executed. The words “An amount greater than that authorized for a fiscal year” are substituted for “Funds . . . in excess of limitations imposed under the preceding sentence with respect to a fiscal year, or for fiscal years after the fiscal year ending ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1983","children":[],"tail":"” to eliminate unnecessary and obsolete words. The words “under this section” are omitted as surplus. The words “amount authorized” are substituted for “limitation under such sentence” for consistency."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcb3cd76f-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idcb3cd770-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s24902"},"text":"Section 24902 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsecs. (a)(1), (2)(A), (E), was amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/134/tIV/s405/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–134, title IV, § 405(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-12-02"},"text":"Dec. 2, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/2586"},"text":"111 Stat. 2586","children":[],"tail":", and, as so amended, subsec. (a) of that section was repealed and subsecs. (b), (j), and (m) were redesignated (a), (g), and (j), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-02-28"},"text":"February 28, 1975","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/6"},"text":"Public Law 94–6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/11"},"text":"89 Stat. 11","children":[],"tail":"), referred to in subsec. (b), provided appropriations for interim operating assistance for Federal Railroad Administration of Department of Transportation in chapter II which is not classified to the Code."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 602 of the Rail Passenger Service Act, referred to in subsec. (c), was classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t45/s602"},"text":"section 602 of Title 45","children":[],"tail":", Railroads, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/533/s7/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–533, § 7(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/3519"},"text":"106 Stat. 3519","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcb3cd771-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"idcb3cd772-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“William H. Gray III 30th Street Station” substituted for “30th Street Station” in subsec. (a)(1)(C)(xviii) pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/158/s2"},"text":"section 2 of Pub. L. 113–158","children":[],"tail":", set out below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/158"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–158","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1838"},"text":"128 Stat. 1838","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/113/158"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“SECTION 1.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" REDESIGNATION.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“The railroad station located at 2955 Market Street in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, commonly known as ‘30th Street Station’, shall be known and designated as the ‘William H. Gray III 30th Street Station’.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“SEC. 2.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" REFERENCES.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Any reference in a law, map, regulation, document, paper, or other record of the United States to the railroad station referred to in section 1 shall be deemed to be a reference to the ‘William H. Gray III 30th Street Station’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
